SIMPLE: weedy
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Weedy
<hw>Weed"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Weedier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Weediest</adjf>.]</amorph>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to weeds; consisting of
weeds.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Weedy</xex> trophies.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Abounding with weeds; <as>as, <ex>weedy</ex>
grounds; a <ex>weedy</ex> garden; <ex>weedy</ex> corn.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>See from the <qex>weedy</qex> earth a rivulet break.</q>
<rj><qau>Bryant.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Scraggy; ill-shaped; ungainly; -- said of colts or
horses, and also of persons.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weedy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Weedy
<hw>Weed"y</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Dressed in weeds, or mourning
garments.</def> <mark>[R. or Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She was as <qex>weedy</qex> as in the early days of her
mourning.</q> <rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1639 -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Week</ent>⟦br⟧
